values:
Yeah, I know I haven't written in a while.  I also know that I'm tired of making up excuses.

   There's no need to go into details, particularly at the tender stages I am currently in, but I have found a new crush and new fun.  I have also found a new favorite song.  The weirdest thing about this song was that I heard it on the radio the day after I met this guy, and got it stuck in my head so bad that it was there until I saw him again, a week later (today.)  And that song is so perfect that I decided I would include it in here in its entirety; please excuse me if I have offended the rights of the band or somesuch nonsense (stupid if you ask me; essentially I am promoting their song.)

   It's by COUNTING CROWS and it's called "Accidentally in Love."

"So she said what's the problem baby
What's the problem I don't know
Well maybe I'm in love (love)
Think about it every time
I think about it
Can't stop thinking 'bout it

"'How much longer will it take to cure this
Just to cure it cause I can't ignore it if it's love (love)
Makes me wanna turn around and face me but I don't know nothing 'bout love

"Come on, come on
Turn a little faster
Come on, come on
The world will follow after
Come on, come on
Cause everybody's after love

"So I said I'm a snowball running
Running down into the spring that's coming all this love
Melting under blue skies
Belting out sunlight
Shimmering love

"Well baby I surrender
To the strawberry ice cream
Never ever end of all this love
Well I didn't mean to do it
But there's no escaping your love

"These lines of lightning
Mean we're never alone,
Never alone, no, no

"Come on, Come on
Move a little closer
Come on, Come on
I want to hear you whisper
Come on, Come on
Settle down inside my love

"Come on, come on
Jump a little higher
Come on, come on
If you feel a little lighter
Come on, come on
We were once
Upon a time in love

"We're accidentally in love
Accidentally in love [x7]

"Accidentally

"I'm In Love, I'm in Love,
I'm in Love, I'm in Love,
I'm in Love, I'm in Love,
Accidentally [x2]

"Come on, come on
Spin a little tighter
Come on, come on
And the world's a little brighter
Come on, come on
Just get yourself inside her

"Love ...I'm in love"

Well, here goes.  I haven't written enough in here, and I could come up with a hundred excuses and then a hundred more, but what it all comes down to is being lazy.  Well, being lazy in what little time I have had.  See, it seems to me that lately, what with all of these Physics projects and that procrastination project in Government and Politics, I have been living at the school more than I have been living at home.  Factor in Tae Kwon Do classes and studying for finals, and I have had precious little time.  By the time I have time (if there is enough time for your thoughts to make sense of the tangled meanings of time) I am typically so exhausted from working all day that I lay there staring at my ceiling for a few minutes, and then pass out and drool on my pillow for the rest of the night.

   So that sums up my excuses, now I will write and get it over with.  I haven't even mentioned anything about prom, because, well, frankly, I have not written since before prom, and that was over a month ago.  Oops.  Anyway, prom was awesome, I was spoiled rotten by my date, who refused to let me pay for anything (the limo, the ticket, the pictures, the keychains... he threw my money back at me for the latter.)  Dancing was more than I could have wished for, and there are many fond memories thus associated.

   Then there comes the weird stuff.  Starting with yesterday.  Yesterday, to put it simply, sucked.  It started off with me finding out that I was not accepted to be a cashier at the Mystic Aquarium.  That just proves I am inept.  If I cannot be a cashier, of all things, then what could I be?  So I had it in my mind that morning that it was going to be a Bad Luck day.  Well, frankly, I was right.

   I finally got the nerve up yesterday to ask the guy I liked if he liked me.  (Childish games that everyone plays in high school.)  I did it, and was shaking like a timebomb about to explode.  That's what my head felt like.  Then I found out that the certain guy did not want a relationship because college is only a year away.  So frickin' what?  Leastaways, that's what I was thinking.  Then I realized, through the way he was talking, that his lack of emotion which I had earlier attributed to his shyness was really that he is so stoic as to bury everything before it has a chance to evolve.  What hurt me the most was how disillusioned I was when I realized what he really was.  So I went on with my day, and felt numb and confused and artificially happy for the rest of it.

   Just when I was thinking that I wasn't even going to shed more than a tear or two, which I had dropped earlier, it hit me.  I was about to go to sleep.  I shut off my light and lay down, and then it suddenly felt like the world landed on top of me.  I think I imploded, and then I burst into tears.  As I was having my cry, alone in the dark and needing a hug, I looked out my window and saw a ton of fireflies.  Normally, I would have just been, oh, fireflies, that's nice, because they're usually in the very back of our backyard, near the woods, where I can hardly see them.  Now, they were swarming all around our house, and particularly by my window.  Perhaps it was just coincidence, but being a strong believer in fateful coincidences, I felt like it was something more.  Randomly, a line of a particular song came into my mind.  "I'll give you a daisy a day, dear, I'll give you a daisy a day, I'll love you until the rivers run still, and the four winds we know blow away."  And it just struck me as fitting, and a few more tears leaked out, and then I gave up, took some benedryl (blame it on my allergies) and hit the sack for the night.

   Today, I woke up and it was oh so sticky and muggy, how simply disgusting.  The day was uneventful as far as normal days are concerned, and I kind of moped my way through it.  When I got home, I went into my backyard to pick some flowers in hopes that they would make me feel better.  I saw one by this particular rock in my backyard that I have always thought of as lucky since I was little (no reason why).  I went over to it, and picked the flower, which was a daisy.  At that moment, I remembered the song I had been thinking last night, and my heart felt like it was going to overflow.  On impulse, I kissed the flower- it seemed like it was a lucky flower.  I wandered the yard, carefully looking for other daisies so I could make a bouquet and put it in my room.  There were no other daisies.

   "I'll give you a daisy a day, dear, I'll give you a daisy a day..."

   It was the Daisy of the Day.  It was not there yesterday.  There are no other daisies.  I will be scared if there is another daisy all by itself tomorrow.

   I walked back to my house, twirling the daisy in my fingertips.  The song still played in my head.

   "I'll love you until the rivers run still, and the four winds we know blow away..."

   This verse ran through my head loudly, powerfully, and I got all choked up again and the tears sneaked out from under my sunglasses. 

   Moral of this story?  I am a sap, proud of it, and in love with daisies.

-M

Yeah yeah, so maybe it's true that I started this journal back in the end of March, and this is my second entry, in early May... Therefore everyone in the world can see just how much of a slacker I really am.  But hey, there you have it; you can't have everything.  Apparently for me, time is among the list of such things.  Wow, I have been so busy lately that I have barely had time to sleep, let alone think about doing something constructive like keeping on top of this journal (which, by the way, still confuses me...)
     The good news is, however, that our Junior Prom is just over 11 days away!  Maybe I'm overreacting, and getting overly excited, but hey, what can I say; I am a girl and it is my right.  I actually have been looking forward to Prom since, well, to be truthful, the beginning of the year.  A month and a half ago, I finally got up the nerve and asked someone to go... no sense in going into details- that borders too close on personal information... in other words, stuff I'd rather not post on the internet.
     The bad news is... well, I don't know, perhaps that I have an AP Calculus test THIS WEDNESDAY that I'm going to fail because our teacher is inept...  Oh well, lucky for me, our school worked out this nice deal that you can get two AP tests for the price of one.  For those unable to follow my incohesive thought pattern (this list includes myself, of course) what I mean is that I won't be out the $82 on the test- wahoo!  Oh well, I really can't see as I have a prayer of passing.  <Receives a mental slap from friend Katie>  Damn, I mean, of course, I am an optimistic person, <cough> therefore, yeah, that's right, I'm gonna kick some booty on that test!!!
     Hmmm, let's see.  What else is on my mind?  Something about Prom, naturally, and then- oh!  I have to play my flute at the Chorus Concert this Thursday!  Everybody come watch me make a fool of myself as I try to keep those a capella singers on pitch!  Mental note, do not laugh when conductor motions for the girls to drop their jaws to keep from going sharp- sudden snorting staccato notes on the flute would be less than savory...
     Another mental note (and to all those out there who are as bad with computers as I am...) do NOT press the tab key while typing online...  Forget paragraph indentation, try accidentally aborting the entire thing you were just typing.  Don't get me started on that one... oh boy, we'll just leave it that e-mail can be a royal pain in the ass sometimes...
     Damn, but I won't forget that one... I just pressed tab AGAIN for like, the fifth time.  Not, of course, that any of those few (choice few, I fear) of you reading this really even care about my nonsensical interjections.
     And to that guy who is just that good... you know who I'm talking to...  I promise that from now on I will try not to slack so much on the journal-thing and yes, you are right, it can be very amusing at times.
     Effin A, I've about had it with that tab key!!!
     Oh, er, um, excuse me.  <clears throat and hopes no one is paying attention>
     Well, there, I think that about does it.  If I forgot to mention anything, it will come out when my next book (er, I mean, journal entry) is published (er, I mean, updated)...  Farewell to any who have read this (I don't know if there are any...) and may your eyes uncross and sense enter your brains after you leave my mind games to myself.



M

So here it is: my first ever entry in a journal that I have no idea how to use. I'm hoping that eventually I'll get the hang of it. I really have no clue what I'm supposed to be saying, so I guess the best thing to do is to close my eyes, cross my fingers, and... well, seeing as I'm typing, it may make more sense if I crossed my toes instead (it's kind of difficult to type with crossed fingers.) Anyway, my point being that I guess I'll just say whatever comes to my mind at the time. Therefore I shall have a reasonable representation of my randomness and abstract humor that most people (including myself) do not get. Oh, well, c'est la vie, or so the French say.

     At any rate, I believe that it is impossible to get anything that comes even close to making sense out of me at this particularly late hour, so I will conclude for now, and perhaps write again in the near future when my brain is more functional and I have a bit more knowledge on how to operate this enigma of an online journal.
